Series II, Writings, contains drafts for poems, novels, theatrical adaptations, and other writings by Solange Clésinger-Sand. There are complete manuscripts for the early "Les roses et une fauvette..." (1834), "Histoirettes pour les toute petits," and a travelogue entitled "Une visite à Charon", in addition to a number of drafts for incomplete projects, including a play ("Sélim"), a theatrical adaptation ("Orio Soranzo") of a novel (
                     L'Uscoque
                  ) by George Sand, and a novel, [On Thora]. Writings also contain notes and manuscript fragments.

Material relating to Villa Malgrétout, named after the novel (
                     Malgrétout
                  ) by her mother, consists of correspondence, plans, and financial and legal documents.
